During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki addressed questions about President Biden's statements regarding the advice of his military advisors on the withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan. Psaki clarified that there were differing viewpoints among the advisors, and the President ultimately made the decision not to continue the troop presence due to the risks and potential casualties involved. She emphasized that the President welcomes a range of advice but ultimately has the authority to make decisions in the best interest of the United States. Psaki also discussed the ongoing negotiations on the reconciliation bill, stating that the President is committed to getting both the infrastructure bill and the reconciliation package passed. She acknowledged that there are differing viewpoints among Democrats on the topline number for the reconciliation package and that the President is listening to various perspectives. Psaki also addressed questions about the energy crisis, the debt limit, and the meetings with African leaders.